<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-01-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="80" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4737/36.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Brazil</gloss>
                                to President <persName type="to">Taft</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-01-18"><hi rend="italic">January 18,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Cordially thank you for condolences which in your name and that of the
                            American people you were so good as to send me on the occasion of the
                            death of Ambassador Joaquim Nabuco.</p>
                        <p>The Brazilian Nation and its Government receive with keen appreciation
                            the demonstrations of sympathy with which the United States of America
                            join us in our great grief over the loss that Brazil and the cause of
                            Pan Americanism have just suffered.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Nilo Pecanha.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>